I can only guess at what is going on because your `initComponents()` method is missing from the supplied code. If nothing is happening when a seat button is clicked up then we can obviously come to some conclusion that the `buttonActionPerformedCommon()` method is not getting called when a seat button is selected. At this point I can only suggest the following which I would like you to **try**...

**-: Make a backup of your application :-**

Create an *Inner Class* Within your **Chart** class and name it **SeatingActionListener**, for example:

```
public class Chart extends javax.swing.JFrame {
   
    // Arraylist of Type Seat
    public static ArrayList&lt;Seat&gt; allSeats;
    
    Public static File nameSave;
    

    // Constructor
    public Chart() {
        initComponents();
    }

    // -----------------------------------------------------
    // .....   All The Rest Of Your Chart Class Code   .....
    // -----------------------------------------------------
    
    // Inner Class (SeatingActionListener):
    class SeatingActionListener implements java.awt.event.ActionListener {
        @Override
        public void actionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt) {
            if (evt.getSource() instanceof javax.swing.JButton) {
                javax.swing.JButton button = (javax.swing.JButton) evt.getSource();
                String seatNumber = button.getActionCommand();

                /* Call the `buttonActionPerformedCommon()` method.
                   Notice how this method now only has two parameters 
                   instead of three. The `evt` ActionEvent parameter
                   wasn&#39;t doing anything anyways. It really shouldn&#39;t
                   be required. Who hey, who knows...you may need it
                   need for something in which case you can just add
                   the parameter back in if you like.             */
                buttonActionPerformedCommon(button, seatNumber);
            }

        }
    }


}
```

Declare this listener within the members area of your **Chart** class, for example:

    public class Chart extends javax.swing.JFrame {
   
